<cc:SdkSinglePageViewer
  Name    ="_ef30ab78_d334_4668_917d_c9f66c3b6aea"
  Tag     ="x:ClassModifier Attribute"
  xmlns:cc="clr-namespace:Microsoft.Windows.SdkViewer.Controls;assembly=SdkViewer"
  xmlns   ="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation">
  <FlowDocument xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation">
    <Table CellSpacing="5">
      <TableRowGroup>
        <TableRow>
          <TableCell>
            <Paragraph FontSize="22"><Run>x:ClassModifier Attribute</Run>

            </Paragraph>

          </TableCell>

        </TableRow>

      </TableRowGroup>

    </Table>

    <Paragraph>Modifies XAML compilation behavior in cases where <Run FontWeight="Bold">x:Class</Run>
 is also provided. Specifically, instead of creating a partial class with a Public access level (the default), the provided <Run FontWeight="Bold">x:Class</Run>
 is created with a NonPublic access value.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22"><Run>Dependencies</Run>

    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph><Hyperlink NavigateUri="bc4a3d8e-76e2-423e-a5d1-159a023e82ec.xaml">x:Class Attribute</Hyperlink>
 must also be provided on the same element, and that element must be the root element in a page.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22"><Run>Remarks</Run>

    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph>The exact string to pass varies depending on the language being used. That string depends on how each language implements its CodeDomProvider to type-convert the values for TypeAttributes.Public and TypeAttributes.NonPublic, and whether that language is case sensitive or not. For C#, the string to pass to designate NonPublic is <Run FontWeight="Bold">internal</Run>
.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph>You can also specify Public (<Run FontWeight="Bold">public</Run>
 in C# ) but that is uncommon, because that is already the default.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22"><Run>Example Attribute Usage</Run>

    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph>
&lt;<Run FontStyle="italic">object</Run>
<Run FontWeight="Bold">x:Class</Run>
="<Run FontStyle="italic">namespace.classname</Run>
" <Run FontWeight="Bold">x:ClassModifier</Run>
="internal">
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph>...
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph>
&lt;/<Run FontStyle="italic">object</Run>
>
    </Paragraph>

